Package Model

Class CacheState

java.lang.Object
Model.CacheState
public class CacheState extends Object
The CacheState class represents the state of the cache at a specific point in a cache simulation. It includes information such as cache sets, access counts, total access time, set index, and block index.

  • Constructor Details

    • CacheState

      public CacheState(List<CacheSet> cacheSets, int cacheHits, int cacheMisses, int setSize, double totalAccessTime, int setIndex, int randBlockIndex, int data)
      Constructor for the CacheState class. Creates a new CacheState object with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      cacheSets - The list of cache sets representing the state of the cache.
      cacheHits - The number of cache hits in the cache state.
      cacheMisses - The number of cache misses in the cache state.
      setSize - The size of each set in the cache.
      totalAccessTime - The total access time in the cache state.
      setIndex - The index of the cache set in the cache state.
      randBlockIndex - The index of the randomly selected block in the cache set during a replace operation.
      data - The data being processed in the cache state.
